{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"creat"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"mode"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On POSIX systems file descriptors are implemented by the operating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"system. On Windows, it’s the C library that implements ","type":"text"},{"code":"creat()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file descriptors. The actual Windows API for opening files is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"different, see MSDN documentation for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CreateFile()"},{"type":"text","text":". The Win32 API"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"uses file handles, which are more randomish integers, not small","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"integers like file descriptors.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because file descriptors are specific to the C library on Windows,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the file descriptor returned by this function makes sense only to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions in the same C library. Thus if the GLib-using code uses a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"different C library than GLib does, the file descriptor returned by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this function cannot be passed to C library functions like "},{"code":"write()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"read()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See your C library manual for more details about "},{"code":"creat()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"creat(filename:mode:)","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"func","roleHeading":"Function","externalID":"s:4GLib5creat8filename4modeSiSPys4Int8VGSg_SitF","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"creat"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"mode","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"A wrapper for the POSIX ","type":"text"},{"code":"creat()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"creat()"},{"type":"text","text":" function is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"used to convert a pathname into a file descriptor, creating a file","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if necessary.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":